-- Sino Union Energy Starts Madagascar Second-Phase Drilling, Le Midi Says
-- B y   H a n n a h   M c N e i s h
-- 2010-10-04T07:56:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/sino-union-energy-starts-madagascar-second-phase-drilling-le-midi-says.html
Sino Union Energy Investment Group
Ltd.  has started the second phase of exploratory drilling in a
block in south west Madagascar, Le Midi reported, citing Mining
and Oil Minister  Mamy Ratovomalala .  The Chinese company began drilling in block 3113 to an
expected depth of about 4,450 meters and will announce its
findings within four months, the Antananarivo-based newspaper
today cited Ratovomalala as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah McNeish in Antananarivo via Johannesburg at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
